<geoCoordinate id="1E32736E5439FB1B7843D99D1DFE3924" degrees="28" direction="north" minutes="53" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="28.883333">28°53'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="11BD925CE8B32F01B09DA67E2D59FB5B" degrees="102" direction="west" minutes="28" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-102.46667">102°28'W</geoCoordinate>
, 5200 ft [1590 m], 8 May 1981, D.H.Riskind 2391 (TEX♀).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6BE93509DE9B10B78329AD53BFD27144" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="3BBDB6E48EAEFC4F5B5B33C3524A4103" bold="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Discussion.</emphasis>
This is the most widespread but least common subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="A29064D7FC1080D4EB08BB13101AEC0F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fendleriana">
<emphasis id="5E289A366512CA1A3F2F5F2877F28965" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Poa fendleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Mexico. Staminate plants are rare or absent, except in Coahuila where a staminate plant has been collected. 
<emphasis id="CAFAC89597C7F399817DEAC0016DAD3A" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Poa fendleriana</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="4A94421784C0D62036FC78A091049751" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">fendleriana</emphasis>
intergrades with 
<taxonomicName id="A33F1C11C15707E5DABE2EA245C92827" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fendleriana">
<emphasis id="07D303EE4EBEA5C7358099DECB37E1EA" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Poa fendleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="F87B816192072EDFAB4BBB59154E3FA6" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">albescens</emphasis>
in Chihuahua and in southeast Arizona and southwest New Mexico.
</paragraph>
